2. Types of Normal Forms (These are enough for freshers + most industry cases)
You must know:
1️. 1NF (First Normal Form)
2️. 2NF (Second Normal Form)
3️. 3NF (Third Normal Form)

𝟭𝗡𝗙 (𝗙𝗶𝗿𝘀𝘁 𝗡𝗼𝗿𝗺𝗮𝗹 𝗙𝗼𝗿𝗺) - AtomIC Values
Rules:
- No repeating groups
- No multiple values in one column
- Each column must be atomic (single value)
 
𝐍𝐨𝐭 𝐢𝐧 𝟏𝐍𝐅
property_id | amenities
1           | gym, pool

𝐈𝐧 𝟏𝐍𝐅
property_id | amenity
1           | gym
1           | pool
Ikkada Meaning
=> Each cell should contain only one value/atomic/unique value

𝟮𝗡𝗙 (𝗦𝗲𝗰𝗼𝗻𝗱 𝗡𝗼𝗿𝗺𝗮𝗹 𝗙𝗼𝗿𝗺)
Rule chudu:
- Must be in 1NF
- No partial dependency(When a column depends on only part of a composite key, not the full key)

Problem Example
(property_id, owner_id) -> owner_name
Owner name depends only on owner_id, not full key

Solution entantee
Split table:

Property Table
property_id | owner_id

Owner Table
owner_id | owner_name
Ikkada Every column must depend on the entire primary key

Inkoo example: (order_id, product_id) -> product_name
Fix:
- Orders table 
- Products table

𝟯𝗡𝗙 (𝗧𝗵𝗶𝗿𝗱 𝗡𝗼𝗿𝗺𝗮𝗹 𝗙𝗼𝗿𝗺)
Rule
- Must be in 2NF
- No transitive dependency (A -> B -> C So A indirectly determines C)

Problem Example
property_id -> locality -> city
City depends on locality, not directly on property

Solution chudandi:
Properties
property_id | locality_id

Locality Table
locality_id | locality | city
Meaning: Non-key columns should not depend on other non-key columns

 Normalization    | Denormalization 
 Less redundancy  | More redundancy 
 More joins       | Fewer joins     
 Better integrity | Faster reads    
 Complex queries  | Simple queries  

 Normal Form         Rule                     
 1NF         | Atomic values            
 2NF         | No partial dependency    
 3NF         | No transitive dependency 

Finalga Step-by-Step Example chudu: (Like you need to solve in real Interviews)
Always follow this approach:
1️. Identify redundancy/Duplicates and remove it
2️. Check 1NF -> atomic values
3️. Check 2NF -> partial dependency
4️. Check 3NF -> transitive dependency
5️. Split tables properly

Original Table
property_id | locality | city | owner_name | owner_phone | rent
Step 1 - 1NF: Ensure atomic values (already fine)

Step 2 - 2NF: Remove partial dependency:
Properties
property_id | owner_id | locality | rent
Owners
owner_id | owner_name | owner_phone

Step 3 - 3NF: Remove transitive dependency:
property_id -> locality_id -> city
Properties
property_id | owner_id | locality_id | rent
Owners
owner_id | owner_name | owner_phone
Locality
locality_id | locality | city

𝗔𝗻𝗼𝘁𝗵𝗲𝗿 𝗲𝘅𝗮𝗺𝗽𝗹𝗲: 𝗦𝘁𝘂𝗱𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗖𝗼𝘂𝗿𝘀𝗲𝘀
